        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 8:02AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 801 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
southeastern Clear Lake, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southern Pasadena, southeastern Pearland, League City, Friendswood,
La Porte, Dickinson, South Houston, Seabrook, Webster, Kemah, South
Belt / Ellington, Clear Lake, Greater Hobby Area, Nassau Bay, Taylor
Lake Village, El Lago, Shoreacres, Clear Lake Shores, Edgebrook Area,
and The Johnson Space Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
